Class MultiValidationRuleFieldDefinitionDTO

java.lang.Object
uk.pallas.systems.typr.rest.entities.v1.AbstractFieldDefinitionDTO
uk.pallas.systems.typr.rest.entities.v1.MultiValidationRuleFieldDefinitionDTO
All Implemented Interfaces:
uk.pallas.systems.typr.entities.v1.FieldDefinition, uk.pallas.systems.typr.entities.v1.MultiValidationRuleFieldDefinition
public class MultiValidationRuleFieldDefinitionDTO extends AbstractFieldDefinitionDTO implements uk.pallas.systems.typr.entities.v1.MultiValidationRuleFieldDefinition
The idea of a rule wrapper is to allow us to hold different rules for a field definition, for example postal code is different within each country (e.g. UK Post Code, USA Zip Code, etc..). Similary some things are a construction of other fields (e.g. Hostname will often have a Top Level Domain name included).

  • Method Details

    • isValid

      public boolean isValid(Object toTest)
      Is the supplied test object something that matches against our field definition regular expression? If validation optional is set to true this will return true, if the supplied object is null, this will always return false. Other-wise this will call toString and then match the field definition regex tp confirm the object matches our desired value.
      Specified by:
